#
# Package Manager Documentation: pacman
# Base Distro: Arch Linux
#

pacman -S  	<package-name> : To Install a package
pacman -Ss 	<package-name> : To search for a package in the repository
pacman -Q  	<package-name> : To search for a package in the installed list; Leave empty to print all installed packages
pacman -Qq 	<package-name> : To search for a package in the installed list formatted without version; Leave empty to print all installed packages without version
pacman -R	<package-name> : To remove a package installed without removing any other dependencies
pacman -Rsu <package-name> : To remove a package alongside all dependencies; recommended for uninstallations.

